    "en": {
      "title": "standoff with the police; City council member arrested",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Vunia - Due to the tense situation between government employees and the police at the petrol filling station located on Mannar Road today (18), Vunia Municipal Council member M.S. Two people, including Abdul Bari, have been arrested by the police.",
        "For the past four days, government officials and public have been waiting in a queue day and night to get fuel at the petrol station under the Nelukulam police division.",
        "In this case, more than fifty policemen formed a new line for themselves and engaged in the process of getting fuel.",
        "Also, there was a tension between the government employees and the police as they said that the government employees can get fuel only after the police get their own fuel.",
        "In addition, the police had arrested a member of the city council and a government official who had contacted the police in this regard.",
        "This caused great confusion in the area and two policemen; The chaos ended only after the police agreed to supply the fuel as two civil servants.",
        "At the same time, the public reports that they have to wait for more than several days to get their fuel because the police get fuel on a special priority basis while distributing fuel at the fuel filling stations."
      ],
